FBIS3-31481 "dreeu034__a94002" FBIS-EEU-94-034-A Document Type:Daily Report 18 February 1994 ANNEX Bulgaria Burgas Port Offers To Handle Thessaloniki Trade AU1802085694 Sofia BTA in English 2315 GMT 17 Feb 94 AU1802085694 Sofia BTA Language: English Article Type:BFN ["Today" -- BTA lead] [Excerpts] Sofia, February 17 (BTA) -- According to Minister of Transport Kiril Ermenkov, the future West-East transport corridor is a very serious project and it has good prospects for development during the application of sanctions against ex-Yugoslavia. Mr. Ermenkov is taking part in the meeting of the transport ministers of Albania, Italy, Macedonia, Turkey and Bulgaria that opened today. The transport ministers gathered to consider the prospects for building the corridor. Starting from Italy's southern ports and crossing the Balkan countries, the transport corridor is expected to provide an alternative connection between Western and Central Europe on the one hand and the Middle east and the former Soviet republics on the other. [passage omitted] The Black Sea port of Burgas is ready to take over the servicing of Macedonia's exports and imports, the Press Service of Port Burgas announced. The port authorities adopted the decision in connection with press reports that Greece had banned Macedonia from using the port of Thessaloniki for its commerce. All interested companies conducting trade with Macedonia can use the services of port Burgas, the announcement says. [passage omitted]
